3(x^2)(e^{-2/x^2}-1)
3x^2(e^{-2/x^2}-1)=3x^2\left(1-\frac{2}{x^2}+O\left(\frac1{x^4}\right)-1\right)=-6+O\left(\frac1{x^2}\right)\xrightarrow{x\to\infty}-6
e^{f(x)} = \sum\limits_{n = 0}^{\infty} \dfrac{(f(x))^n}{n!}
3x^2(e^{-2/x^2} - 1)
e^y=\sum_{n=0}^\infty{\frac{y^n}{n!}}
y=-2/x^2
e^{-2/x^2}=\sum_{n=0}^\infty{\frac{-2^n}{(n!)x^{2n}}}
3\sum_{n=0}^\infty{\frac{-2^n}{(n!)x^{2n-2}}}-3x^2=3\sum_{n=1}^\infty{\frac{-2^n}{(n!)x^{2n-2}}}
